page.title: 04SETTLEMENTS-WOOD END
page.content: {Wood End} comprises 29 houses. At the foot of a rise stands the old Post House, now a private residence. This thatched house dates from the Stuart period, possibly 1605. Mains electricity & water were installed in February 1985. The present owners moved in in October 1984. At the top of the rise stands Wood End House, rebuilt about 150 years ago. The stables have been converted and the property stands in 17 acres. The Lodge at the drive entrance is very old, revealing walls of wattle and daub.
